{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c8b66d20-36cf-4ec0-bf3e-edefb9b5d11d","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`** for hot reload.\n\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-runs tests automatically when files change.\n- **`dotnet watch run`** — restarts/hot-reloads an app on changes.\n\nPlain `dotnet test` and `dotnet run` are one-shot commands; they don't watch for file changes or apply hot reload.\n\nSince your project appears to be a test project, you'd want:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\nThis will monitor your source files and re-execute tests whenever you save a change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3ff09871-6026-490d-98ba-400b30e108cc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about hot reload in .NET - specifically whether they should use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` to benefit from hot reload. Let me look at the project files to understand the context.","outputTokens":196,"requestId":"0839:2F47F1:D2A742:F58350:69EAC987"},"id":"70987f7f-644b-4925-b05b-a9045176241e","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:38:21.116Z","parentId":"a34d3e16-df11-4029-bcc7-a20844bb26a5"}
